# View Tiddlers

View tiddlers are regular wikitext tiddlers that render inside layout slots. They are assigned via `appify-view-<slot>` fields on the app tiddler.

## Binding a view to a slot

```
set_field(title="<appTitle>", field="appify-view-sidebar", value="MyApp/sidebar-view")
```

## Reading a view's source

Use `get_tiddler(title)` to read the full wikitext. This is what you modify with `set_field(field="text")`.

## Common wikitext patterns in views

### Navigation list (clickable items that set a channel)
```
<$list filter="Alpha Bravo Charlie">
<$button>
<$action-statewrap-set channel="project" value=<<currentTiddler>>/>
<<currentTiddler>>
</$button>
</$list>
```

### Conditional rendering (show content based on channel)
```
<%if [statewrap-get[project]!is[blank]]%>
  Project is selected: <$text text={{{[statewrap-get[project]]}}}/>
<%else%>
  Select a project
<%endif%>
```

### Tab buttons (mutually exclusive selection)
```
<$button class={{{ [statewrap-get[tab]match[overview]then[active]else[]] }}}>
<$action-statewrap-set channel="tab" value="overview"/>
Overview
</$button>
```

### Reveal panel (show/hide based on channel value)
```
<$reveal stateTitle={{{[statewrap-ref[tab]]}}} type="match" text="overview">
  Content for overview tab
</$reveal>
```

### Dynamic macro-based data
```
\define items-Alpha() Design Build Test
\define items-Bravo() Research Plan Execute

<$set name="proj" value={{{[statewrap-get[project]]}}}>
<$list filter="[<proj>addprefix[items-]getvariable[]enlist-input[]]" variable="item">
  <<item>>
</$list>
</$set>
```
This pattern stores data in macros keyed by channel value.

## Modifying a view

1. Read current wikitext with get_tiddler
2. Understand the structure (macros, lists, reveals, channels used)
3. Write updated wikitext with set_field(field="text", value="new wikitext")

Important: Preserve the existing patterns. If a view uses `\define` macros for data, add new entries in the same pattern. If it uses `$list filter="..."`, add items to that filter.

